{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ef72db9-6415-4cf0-8ff4-827e8b7e6d5c","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c5aeea8-c3a4-429f-88bd-5cbc91a2351f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've already told me what files need changing.","outputTokens":282},"id":"27f16cba-b952-4699-9dee-d38389451ed0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:59:09.382Z","parentId":"aaef4856-c314-4ce8-9b04-f92f61534a76"}
